# Changelog

## v1.2.0 — 2026-05-14

### Fixed
- WebAssembly (`wasm_eh`): `read_cozip(url)` returned memory corruption
  in `shell.duckdb.org`. Direct C++ construction of `ParquetReader` from
  cozip pulled template instantiations not exported by `duckdb-wasm` side
  modules; the dynamic linker resolved them to stubs returning 0, and the
  resulting null dereference leaked low linear memory into query results.
  Refactored `read_cozip` to a SQL table macro composing `read_parquet`
  over the existing `cozip-subfile://` VFS.

### Changed
- `read_cozip` is now a SQL table macro (was a C++ TableFunction). The
  user-facing API is unchanged: `SELECT * FROM read_cozip(p, gdal_vsi := ...)`.
- Geometry columns from GeoParquet sources arrive typed as `GEOMETRY` with
  CRS metadata, instead of raw `BLOB`. This follows `read_parquet`'s
  behaviour, which the new macro path goes through.
- `read_cozip(NULL)` now surfaces as a Parser Error mentioning
  `read_parquet`, since NULL propagates through the macro body before any
  cozip-level scalar runs (was a custom bind-time error).
- `parquet` is now a runtime dependency. Default DuckDB and `duckdb-wasm`
  builds autoload it transparently; embedded harnesses with autoload
  disabled must `LOAD parquet` explicitly.